This place should be monitored by corporate. They get the wrong orders and get an attitude if you ask if yours is coming up. My name was on the screen and when I asked and was told well there's 14 people ahead what do you expect and then she sucked her teeth. The customer service is lacking 100 percent. My smoothie had yogurt for some odd reason but the manager was very kind and replaced it. I really just wanted to be in and out with this being my first public encounter, and to have some food in my stomach but, fail x2. Super hard bagel and a slithering of egg.

Bad attitude from Adam today, the cashier who took my order.  Didn't ask for my rewards card/phone number. Seemed annoyed when I had to ask for a receipt. A little dirtier than most paneras
Love the soups here.

Have been a regular customer at this Panera for over three years, and was grateful that delivery has been avaiilable during the pandemic.  However, accuracy of orders has certainly slipped of late.  In the past couple of months, I have had two orders misdelivered to wrong addresses or wrong person, and missing items from orders.  I understand mistakes a busy times, but attempts to communicate with management have failed.  They do not answer their phones, not even when calling during their preferred non-busy times.  It wouldn't be so bad if they were not already on the expensive side, PLUS adding a $1.00 "convenience  fee" for the inconvenince of incorrect orders, plus delivery charge, plus tip for driver collected before delivery is made.  They have just priced and poor-serviced themselves out of my breakfast and lunch habit.

I'm done with Panera. Ordered a pizza and drink and tipped 30% for delivery since it was raining. I provided detailed instructions on where to park and how to enter the building. Delivery driver arrived with cold pizza and no $3 drink and wouldn't get out of his car to bring it in. Called me to come outside instead, even though he was parked within 5' of the front door. Didn't care he forgot the drink. I've been calling Panera for an hour and no one will answer the phone (something I've experienced at other locations as well). No drink, no refund. They can keep it. Not ordering from Panera again. üëé

When we took it back, they just picked the almonds out (and even left some) instead of remaking it. We had to take it back for a third time, and they were very rude about the situation. Never coming here again.

Guess you have to be a regular to get great customer service.   The lady in front of us clearly had breakfast bagels but we were told rudely, that breakfast was over at 10:30.... it was 11:05.  Would have ordered something else had the employee been kind and friendly.   Oh well,  will spend my dollars elsewhere.
Hot coffee.
Love the cinnamon crunch bagels and free coffee bagels!

Well, the pandemic makes all restaurant experiences a little awkward. But they're pretty good with orders, everything is served fairly quickly. Restrooms are clean.  Right now, when you place your order you get a pager to pick your own food at the counter in the back. I'd suggest grabbing your table and waiting maybe a minute or two after the pager vibrates to avoid people crowding the counter. You may want to order ahead to save time. It takes a few minutes on your phone and I can almost guarantee that your order will be 100% correct versus placing your order at the register. Although, it is rare when they get your order wrong. If they ever do, is usually because another customer took your order. The food is worth it. Really! As a suggestion, because Panera Bread's menu is mostly Carbs, you may want to order the smallest size and then split with someone; just for portion control. You should be able to substitute non-dairy for most drinks. And your order can be fully customized to your liking or dietary restrictions. The menu works much like it does at Starbucks, as far as substitutions go. And please don't be afraid to ask for substitute. They're staff is very friendly and understanding. It may take you a minute to explain what you want but they'll serve you patiently. The bakery options change with the seasons, so you may want to try their pastries every once in a while. So far, they have the best Chai Late I've had. There's also whole loaves of bread that you can ask to be sliced thick or thin. My daughter loves their Mac & Cheese and the sprouted grain bread.

Ordered you pick two salad and sandwich. Salad was okay but not great, as to be expected with Panera. But the sandwich was not a chipotle chicken avocado melt at all like I ordered! It was literally two pieces of plain bread not toasted or anything with half melted American cheese in the middle, barely even warm and wrapped up in soggy paper. I wish I could post the photos I took of it! I have never been so disgusted! So much so I am now rethinking my life choices including ever ordering Panera again, but especially never ordering from/going to this location again! This went straight in the trash. First time I ordered they forgot to give me my cookie I ordered (it was a door dash order) but I made the mistake of giving them a second chance. They did worse this time around. Don't eat here. Panera overall isn't what it used to be sadly.
It's Panera! Always clean environment and  friendly staff.
Great food. Needed paper towel dispenser to work..Hate drying hands on pants before I touch food.
They need to clean the bathroom this is really bad...pee everywhere never seen like this
Very good service, Eldora was very kind she was very cooperative with our orders.  Will visit again and recommend this place!!

Pathetic mask requirement Cant come inside without a mask but it's OK to take it off in order to eat where is the logic people? Had to leave the place. And I'm glad I did. Went to Starbucks next door and got my coffee with out mask. Don't be a sheep people!
Customer service needs to get better. They need to acknowledge incoming customers and be respectful

Do not order online from this store. They constantly forget parts of your order and cannot be reached by phone to fix it. They have never answered when I call. I'm only leaving this review because it is a recurrent issue and I'm sick of it. Today they missed half my order and there was a hair in what did arrive so I was left with no food to eat. It's totally gross to find someone's hair in your food. The in person experience may be different.

Neither side of the sandwich was grilled or toasted...soft white bread. I make sure that I go to the Cotswald location and the food quality is 180 degrees different. I don't see how Panera chain can support a franchise serving such a horrible quality of food (every time we have ordered). I will drive any day in lunch hour traffic before I ever order a delivery or any food from this location. I should have read the reviews because it seems this location doesn't care about their customers or what they spend their money on.
It was nice. I meet family for lunch. Check it out for your self.

After finishing dinner, we decided too have some coffee. My friend suggested Panera Bread. She loves their coffee. When we arrived, it was almost closing time and the coffee dispensers had already been taken in the back for cleaning. The young lady(Khirah) behind the counter was fantastic and went into the back and fixed us 2 cups of freshly brewed coffee. The coffee was as good as my friend had said it would be. The whole interior of the building was brightly lit and extremely clean. Everything was handicap accessible and appeared to be in good working order. If you took the time to read this review, please take a 1/2 second and click like. Thank you.

Delivery from this store is confusing when using Panera app. They use Door Dash for delivery, but the Panera app has no way to track delivery and orders will indicate "delivered" when it has not been delivered. Don't bother calling store; they hung up on us. We called back and Maurice, Steve, and Kema (GM) were all too busy to help us. Going to Yafo...
The service could be better

This was my second time at this location and it was not a good experience. Each employee I spoke with had an attitude, it would be a 1 star if they didn't at least also have some resemblance of manners and customer service here and there. My order had things I didn't order on it (I had asked about the chocolate chip bagel, but then switched it to a different bagel when I didn't really get an answer, and ended up with a chocolate chip muffie on my order and not even a muffie in my bag) Then I was given my bagel without being asked if I wanted it toasted (first time that's ever happened at any Panera I've ever been to) and when I asked for it to be toasted was the first bit of attitude I got, saying ‚Äúyou didn't say you wanted it toasted.‚Äù Like I said though, she didn't keep TOO much of an attitude, although it was definitely still there. Then when I inquired about the incorrect price I was given money back, but it was almost going to be half of what I was owed, I had to state how much it should be and that didn't even include tax. Then when I finally went to sit down to eat, I noticed I had cream cheese a full month past it's expiration date! When I took it back in, I did get an in date replacement, but no other offer or anything, not even an apology! So by the time I got back to my food, my bagel and soup had cooled, but fortunately nothing got stolen while I went to get my new cream cheese. Fortunately, other than the expired cream cheese and the poor customer service, the food was decent enough, which is why I gave 2 stars instead of just 1! Would have been much happier and possibly not upset at all, maybe just a little bothered by the situation, if more than the bare minimum and technicality's had been done about it, if anybody working there seemed like they gave a darn at all, about the service they are providing, that we the customers are paying for! On top of that, my first experience here wasn't much better, the order was also incorrect, missing the avocado in a ‚Äúchipotle chicken AVOCADO melt‚Äù I also received practically the same level of attitude and annoyingly poor quality of customer service. I let it slide and gave the benefit of the doubt the first round because people make mistakes and have off days right, well not when it's 2/2 horrible service and very obvious it because they don't care about the quality of the service they provide! I don't know how they have a 4.1 overall rating, because looking briefly through reviews it looks like I'm not alone with these experiences either.

This store steals from delivery drivers  I had a huge catering order ($300+) yesterday from this location. When I arrived to pick it up, they said the customer called in to add more things on a second order and to leave a generous tip for the driver, and that they merged the orders together so they wouldn't have to assign a second Doordash driver. After I completed the delivery, my app only showed a $2.76 tip. Which is fine, a tip is extra anyway but that is extremely unusual amount for an order that large. So I stopped by the Panera afterwords and they told me yes there should've been a $47 tip that was on the second part. So after a night and day full of back and forth with Doordash and Panera customer service, it's Panera's own customer service that tells me the second part was processed as a store pickup, therefore the tip never entered the Doordash system to get to me, and whatever worker at the store kept it for themselves. That's theft. I know times are hard for a lot of us, but you didn't earn that money. I hope you're proud of yourself. Stay away from this Panera

I am not normally one to write a bad review. I dont like it when people do.  And I am very patient when people are taking my order but: It took the worker sooo long to get our order placed into the computer. When I walked over to look at the pastries she yelled at more for separating from my lunch date (apparently I needed to stand next to him the whole time). She would not let me choose a pastry. The coffee was cold. The service was unacceptable. I love panera but this location is not one I would go back to.

Used to be better managed, It seems orders are moved to ready soon after it has been placed and yet it's being worked on. Food quality is good but compare to other branches this store has room to improve.

I have been a regular patron of this Panera for over four years and have forgiven a lot of mistakes, usually having to do with forgotten food items or missing components to salads...but the food has always tasted fresh and the management has always been friendly and apologetic so I've overlooked these shortcomings.  Sadly last night was unforgivable and I will not be returning.  My order for curbside was not ready after waiting for several minutes past the designated time so I entered and waited at the passthrough window.  The general state of the interior was unkempt and dirty.  The prep cooks wore their masks over their mouths but not their noses, frequently reaching up to adjust their masks or wipe their faces with gloved hands and then scooping their hands into salad materials or deli meats. While waiting I was casually informed they were out of bread (??) and I would be receiving chips with my soups and when the order was finally ready after getting into my car I realized the grilled cheese wasn't included in the bag.  Upon returning and informing the employees I was missing my grilled cheese they casually responded "I know" and handed me a crumpled wad of brown paper, presumably with the grilled cheese in it. Frankly this last issue was the wake up call I needed to realize this place is a health hazard.  I came to my senses and returned the food to the front counter, leaving empty handed.  Last night my family and I were all a little hungry but at least we weren't risking our health.  If the above review doesn't concern you and you would still like to patronize this place, please take my seasoned advice and always review your pickup order in full before leaving the store.  Nine times out of ten there is at least one missing or incorrect item.

Honestly don't bother ordering online or to go here. The last 2 or 3 times going we got our food it took 30+ minutes on off times. We sat for 45 minutes one time waiting for a simple order and when I went to check a girl back there was texting blatantly. This time going to order food it was ‚Äúpreparing‚Äù for 20 minutes and people who ordered after me received there food first. Ill happily drive a little farther to not go here again.

Not everyone is perfect, and during these times everyone is susceptible to frustration; however, today, the manager (or he could've been the proprietor) was very generous. Very encouraging to pay it forward. Thx

I don't mind paying $9.00 for the bowl but not if there is hardly any food in the bowl. This location missed the mark the day I went.  Small portions,  old lettuce,  sandwich looked slapped together.
